ZH: 他整天游手好闲，从来不做任何事情。
EN: He lazes around all day and never does anything.

ZH: 她的丈夫是个游手好闲的人，整天靠她养活。
EN: Her husband is a lazy person who relies on her to support him.

ZH: 你不能整天游手好闲，必须去找工作。
EN: You can't just laze around all day, you need to go find a job.

ZH: 要想成功，就不能游手好闲。
EN: If you want to succeed, you can't be idle.

ZH: 这个家庭的孩子都很游手好闲，从来不做家务。
EN: The children in this family are all lazy and never do household chores.

ZH: 我讨厌游手好闲的人，他们让人感觉很懒散。
EN: I dislike lazy people who laze around all day, they seem so slothful.

ZH: 不要因为父母的财产而游手好闲，你需要自己努力。
EN: Don't be lazy just because of your parents' wealth, you need to work hard on your own.

ZH: 在这个社会上，游手好闲的人是没有前途的。
EN: In this society, lazy people have no future.

ZH: 他不是个游手好闲的人，他一直在努力工作。
EN: He is not a lazy person, he has been working hard.

ZH: 别让你的孩子养成游手好闲的习惯，让他们培养劳动意识。
EN: Don't let your children develop the habit of being lazy, teach them to have a work ethic.

ZH: 她的男朋友是个游手好闲的人，从来不帮她做事。
EN: Her boyfriend is a lazy person who never helps her with anything.

ZH: 我们的员工都很勤劳，没有一个是游手好闲的。
EN: Our employees are all hardworking, none of them are idle.

ZH: 游手好闲是最让人讨厌的习惯之一。
EN: Laziness is one of the most annoying habits.

ZH: 他的朋友们都是游手好闲的纨绔子弟。
EN: His friends are all idle sons of wealthy families.

ZH: 游手好闲的人很容易被社会淘汰。
EN: Idle people are easily eliminated by society.

ZH: 别总被他那些游手好闲的朋友影响，他们是没出息的。
EN: Don't let his lazy friends influence you, they are worthless.

ZH: 这个团队里没有游手好闲的人，大家都在努力工作。
EN: There are no idle people in this team, everyone is working hard.

ZH: 游手好闲只会让自己越来越废物。
EN: Laziness will only make you more and more useless.

ZH: 我们应该鼓励孩子们远离游手好闲的生活方式。
EN: We should encourage children to stay away from the idle lifestyle.

ZH: 游手好闲的人往往没有追求，生活没有目标。
EN: Idle people often have no aspirations, life without goals.
